SIMPLE: lowliness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lowliness
<hw>Low"li*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Lowly</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or quality of being lowly; humility;
humbleness of mind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Walk . . . with all <qex>lowliness</qex> and meekness.</q>
<rj><qau>Eph. iv. 1, 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Low condition, especially as to manner of
life.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>lowliness</qex> of my fortune has not brought me to
flatter vice.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Low-lived</ent>⟦br⟧
